Bodhisattva Ksitigarbha took a great vow to guide all living beings from hell and refused to achieve Buddhahood until all hells were emptied.

This noble commitment has earned him the title of the bodhisattva of hell-beings. Moreover, in Japanese culture, he is regarded as the guardian of children and the patron deity of deceased children and aborted fetuses.

Typically portrayed as a serene monk with a halo encircling his shaved head, K·π£itigarbha carries a staff to forcibly open the gates of hell and a wish-fulfilling jewel that illuminates the darkness.

items.name: Futura Sienna
items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 90%

(Medium quality dataset. Likeness is good despite dataset. Training method could be improved.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 23 images, 5000 steps, and 217 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futurasienna5000v5, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futurasienna5000v5, etc.

    • Sample images were not done this way because I was an amateur.

  • Recommended strength:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • Optional:

    • Negative: nose ring, lying on floor

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.

items.name: Poker card figure
items.description:
TRIGGER WARNING (or aesthetic advice): this model connects body parts to make poker cards, putting in a realistic models will result in bodies with severe deformations (I personnally think this is hilarious, I have seen most movies on this page https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Body_horror ). You can't post them here (considered graphic violence).

This Lora is experimental. See 'Centrosymmetry' in suggested resources, it looks better.

This makes figures that have (approximate) central symmetry, to use as figure for poker cards.

The recommended aspect ratio is 0.6 (this is approximately the aspect ratio on poker cards figures), so 460*768. You might get two figures if you use a square resolution.

Prompt:

  • no activation word

  • helper word: upside down, multiple views, white background, simple background

  • do not prompt for clothing items or body parts under the belt (feet, trousers, dress, legs, ...), it will break the symmetry

  • lora weight: 0.5 to get better drawing (but lots of bad cards), 1.0 to get lots of good symmetry (but blurry faces)

Additional Notes:

  • this was made by rotating the cards in OpenCV and correcting cards by hand (I'm not very good with GIMP so the data isn't top quality). This might require another round of generate/select/train.

  • dataset included

  • as you can see on the images (and on the 'CentroSymmetry' Lora), upside down faces are not very good. You can actually tell whether the generation is going to be good during the generation process, the upside down face must be drawn at the same time as the upper face (and not twice as blurry).

  • I'm stupid, the danbooru tag is rotational_symmetry, but it is mostly 'dual_persona', that is two opposite but related characters

  • added an example of a 'joker' prompt (no rotational symmetry)

items.name: Harakht
items.description:
This is a Hypernetwork based off of a character from an episode of Conan the Barbarian, called An Evil Wind in Kunark. He is based off of an obscure deity from the Stygian pantheon from the Conan the Barbarian novels. He is based loosely on Horus. Depending where you go or look, the name Harak is also shown to be spelled Harakt and Harakht. While known as a falcon or hawk God, the cartoon shows Harak as being a mix of an eagle, hawk, and perhaps even a vulture. Also, he is portrayed as a demon and not a God.

Important thing to know about this Lora: Keep the weight of the Lora at under 0.5. For example, the Lora would look like this <lora:Harakht -000014:0.5> with the numbers at the end changed. Also, I find that the best and most optimal results from from when the weight of the Lora is set at 0.35. Anything above a weight of 0.5 results in increasing levels of erratic looks. At or near 0.5, the images closely resemble the art and style of the animation of the cartoon it came from.

Also to note, when this Lora is used with the Hypernetwork I made, both work best with the Lora set at 0.35 and the Hypernetwork set at a weight from 0.35 to 0.65. When used together, the results resemble the look and art style of the original animation while also a much more cleaner and sophisticated look than if the Lora were used alone.

For the CFG Scale and Denosing Strength, I thus far used the default settings for the program when experimenting with the Lora.

The Lora can be made better for sure, yet I ask for patience on that due to the age of the computer I am using.

items.name: Syoyo - Artist Style
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

Another model trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

This model was made at the suggestion of @madmoon

About the artist:

Instagram: Syoyo (@syooooyoooo) | Instagram

Twitter: Syoyo (@syooooyoooo) / Twitter

Syoyo is an illustrator making highly stylized art deco art. The most recognizable element is the blending of clothes or accessories with the background and the usage of very few different colors.

Weights & Prompts

The only activation prompt is

syoyo

The effect can potentially be enhanced by adding the prompts

art deco, "color" theme

v1.0:

This model is pretty volatile as the dataset of syoyo's current style is pretty small. Thus I was limited to 28 images.

Use a weight of 0.8-0.9. Many of the example images were made with a weight of 1.0 but SD struggles to upscale and fix the face for most of them.

I also recommend creating a larger number of images for each prompt, as it isn't very flexible and doesn't consistently blend the character with the background.

Finally, SD will tend to color large parts fo the image based on the first color in any prompt. So be careful how you construct them. This model really is more for experimenting and seeing what you get than making specific images.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

items.name: Fran Drescher (Look from The Nanny (1993-1999)) - Textual Inversion
items.description:
This ti was requested by @WolfSpider

Fran Drescher is an American actress, comedian, writer, and activist. She is best known for her role as Fran Fine in the popular 1990s television sitcom called "The Nanny," which aired from 1993 to 1999. Her character, Fran Fine, was a cosmetics saleswoman from Queens who becomes the nanny for a wealthy British widower and his three children. items.description:
Support needed ! Out of colab credits. You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

You can also subscribe to my Patreon and get exclusive models .

Xena: Warrior Princess is an American fantasy television series filmed on location in New Zealand. The series aired in first-run syndication from September 4, 1995, to June 18, 2001.

The series narrative follows Xena (played by Lucy Lawless), an infamous warrior on a quest to seek redemption for her past sins against the innocent by using her formidable fighting skills to now help those who are unable to defend themselves. Xena is accompanied by Gabrielle (played by Renee O'Connor), who during the series changes from a simple farm-girl into an Amazon warrior and Xena's soulmate and comrade-in-arms; her initial na√Øvet√© helps to balance Xena and assists her in recognizing and pursuing the greater good.

items.name: Diaper Under Tights LORA v1.0 - Realistic ABDL
items.description:
A LORA for making pretty ladies who are wearing diapers under their tights.

If you like my work you can tip me through Comiss.io.

Someone asked me to make a LORA for this style and it didn't need a huge amount of work so I figured I'd just throw it together and see what happened.

Polite notice: This LORA only depicts adults doing consensual adult things, and fully complies with the TOS at CivitAI.

The trigger is diaper_under_tights and you can prompt for a limited selection of colours (white, black, nude, pink). I recommend running it about 0.9 LORA strength, but adjust to fit your needs. You can also prompt for "front" or "back" if you are struggling to get the figure to face the right way. This version is a bit better, but it still favours drawing ladies from behind.

You cannot prompt for lifted skirts in this version. It sometimes will draw that anyway, because there were some pictures like that in the training data, but you can't really make it happen on purpose. That will be improved in future if/when I can get a bigger and more diverse dataset.

This version seems to have a preference for chubby ladies, but you can prompt for "slim" if that's not to your taste. It also works fine with most prompting for outfits and scenery.

items.name: LahMix Mysterious
items.description:
This is my first checkpoint, and I have tried to merge it through numerous steps starting from Dreamshaper, along with some of my Lora styles, but I can't recall the exact sequence of my work. There have been some changes to the character's face, as well as several elements that have been combined. I have also made several attempts to ensure that the data is not overlapped too much or that the merging process creates inaccurate results.

This is a model completely oriented towards fantasy art style, and it is quite challenging to create realistic forms. It does have some capability, but fundamentally lacks a sense of realism. At least, that's how I feel.

I hope you'll enjoy it as much as I do!

Suggested settings:

  • Clip skip 2,
